    "narrative": "For the Austin Waves on May 2, the outfield anchor remains our clear priority, with **Jackson Merrill** (72.75) and **Kyle Tucker** (72.04) leading the offensive charge. **Jackson Merrill** is a particularly high-leverage start against Burke; his dynamic platoon advantage and a matchup against a pitcher with a \"Slow Delivery\" profile provide an elite environment for him to exploit the stolen base category, which remains our primary focus in this 5x5 format. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from the favorable park factors and the underlying skill projection against McGreevy, making him a cornerstone play. **Drake Baldwin** (67.34) also deserves a mention as a high-floor C1, buoyed by a significant park boost and a top-of-the-order assignment that maximizes his scoring potential despite the matchup against the southpaw Bernardino.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved keeping **Coby Mayo** (52.17) on the bench. While **Coby Mayo** offers excellent power upside and benefits from the same favorable \"Slow Delivery\" context as **Gunnar Henderson** and **Jackson Merrill**, the sheer density of our current middle-infield and corner-infield slots made him the odd man out; he trailed **Jacob Wilson** (60.10) in projected efficiency due to the latter\u2019s superior park and pitcher-skill alignment. We are also keeping a watchful eye on **Josh Lowe** (49.34), who faces a legitimate challenge in McLean; while his platoon edge is strong, his score remains suppressed by the pitcher\u2019s ability to limit production. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a vital piece of the lineup, though owners should be aware that his production is slightly mitigated by the dynamic platoon disadvantage against Weathers, even if his speed profile keeps his floor viable.",
